            "body": "\n> the repro still fails even if I add `vim.api.nvim_set_option_value(\"inccommand\", \"\", {})`.\n\nOk that is good to know.\n\nFor reference, copying my comments from https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/36487 :\n\n- ~~buffer updates should NOT emit during 'inccommand' preview. And the PR should add a small test that verifies this.~~ \n    - Update: I just noticed this in `:help api-buffer-updates` so I guess it's intentional:\n      ```\n      When {changedtick} is |v:null| this means the screen lines (display)\n      changed but not the buffer contents. {linedata} contains the changed\n      screen lines. This happens when 'inccommand' shows a buffer preview.\n      ```\n- a batched buffer update should only be emitted after the user confirms a substitution.\n\n",
